deepLinks.name: Om NOS A/S
deepLinks.snippet: Historien om NOS A/S startede tilbage i 2009, hvor Claus Jensen og Tom Kloster Fyllgraf etablerede virksomheden i et lille kontor på ca. 25 kvm i centrum af Horsens og siden flyttet til Hatting. Historien om NOS A/S er langt fra slut, vi har store ambitioner om at løfte os selv til nye højder.

value.name: Nosy Be, Madagascar: The Complete Guide - TripSavvy
value.snippet: Nosy Be, Madagascar The paradise island of Nosy Be is located off the northwest coast of Madagascar. It is the country’s most popular beach destination, with luxury resorts that overlook perfect stretches of pure white sand and warm, clear waters that provide ample opportunities for scuba diving, snorkeling, and deep-sea fishing.

value.name: Nosy Be - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Nosy Be is Madagascar's largest and busiest tourist resort. It has an area of 320.02 km 2 (123.56 sq mi), and its population was 109,465 according to the provisional results of the 2018 Census. Nosy Be means "big island" in the Malagasy language. The island was called Assada during the early colonial era of the 17th century.

value.name: Nosy Be 2023: Best Places to Visit - Tripadvisor
value.snippet: “Nosy Be?” Is that a typo for “Noisy Bee?” Nope. It means “big island” and it is just that; a large island off the northwest coast of Madagascar. Here you’ll find volcanic lakes, lazy lemurs, rum distilleries, Ylang Ylang plantations and intricate coral reefs that are practically begging to be explored.
